---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About | MindMotion"
  description="MindMotion builds runtime safety software for AI-driven robots."
>
  <Nav />
  <main id="main">
    <Section id="mission" heading="Mission">
      <p>Make robots safe to deploy around people.</p>
    </Section>

    <Section id="approach" heading="Approach">
      <p>
        Capability and trust are different problems. Robots driven by AI become
        more capable through better data, better models, more training. Trust
        does not come from the same place. Trust is established by structure:
        an independent layer that measures, records, and bounds what a robot
        does, regardless of what its AI decides or how it evolves.
      </p>
      <p>We build that layer.</p>
      <p>
        Aviation, automotive, and computing each reached the point where
        execution had to be separated from decision-making. Trust required a
        layer distinct from the system being trusted. Robotics is at the same
        point.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section id="founder" heading="Founder">
      <p>
        MindMotion is led by David Braun. He has spent more than fifteen years
        working on robot control, the field that makes robot motion
        predictable and reliable. His research has produced methods for
        controlling complex robots in the real world, including humanoid
        systems he built and tested. He holds a Ph.D. in mechanical
        engineering. His work has been recognized with the NSF CAREER Award
        and the field's top award for research in robotics.
      </p>
    </Section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>
